channel.description: Rocking the World One Guitar at a Time!

item.title: About
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: One day upon reading through the new Guitar World I noticed a really cool guitar in one of the advertisements. It was Dimebag Darrel Abbot, from Pantera, in an ad for DR Strings. He was playing a Washburn ML, his signature ax, and the body and headstock were covered in aluminum chrome diamond plate. It was the guitar for their Reinventing the Steel Tour and had that inlayed into the fret board. I remember thinking that was a really cool guitar and could not get it out of my mind. Wondering how they did it, I decided to try and build one in my garage/shop only on a smaller scale. I bought an $89.00 Squire from Guitar Center and stripped it completely down to the wood. I picked up a 4x4 sheet of diamond plate  and began cutting. There was a slight learning curve that had to be addressed. How to cut it, how to make the bend, where to have it repainted, find an engraver, and where do I get all the parts? I originally wanted to router off the surface and leave a little lip of wood around the outside and fit the piece of diamond plate into a nice inlay pocket. The wood was crap and the router blew the edges off, so I made a command decision to blend the plate to the rounded edges by beveling the edge of the diamond plate. It worked out much better than I would have hoped. The guitar came out beautiful and FRYONE Signature Series Custom Guitars was born. However as I was in the process of building this guitar a tragedy of epic proportion happened. Dimebag Darrel was murdered. I still get tears in my eyes every time I talk or think about it. I never knew Dime, but I always felt he was my cosmic brother. We were but a couple of months apart in age and it hit home hard, life is so strange. After that it only seemed fitting that this guitar, which was inspired by one of Dime’s guitars, be dedicated to my brother Dime. “Shred In Peace” my brother. My company is dedicated to helping young rocker, like Dime, achieve their goals in an industry that can eat you up and spit you out. That is why our slogan is… “Rocking the World One Guitar at a Time!” John French President FRYONE Signature Series Custom Guitars
